and by earth's light Her hips.

01:21:22.920 --> 01:21:25.999
By Brahma's light her feet came into being;

01:21:26.320 --> 01:21:29.240
by Surya's light Her toes,

01:21:29.480 --> 01:21:34.999
by Vasus's Her fingers, by Kubera's light Her nose;

01:21:35.999 --> 01:21:39.999
by Prajapati's light Her teeth came into being

01:21:40.360 --> 01:21:45.000
and similarly by Agni's light Her three eyes were formed.

01:21:46.400 --> 01:21:50.840
The light of the two sandhyas became her eye-brows,

01:21:50.999 --> 01:21:54.400
the light of Vayu her ears;

01:21:54.999 --> 01:21:58.960
the manifestation of the lights of other devas too

01:21:59.200 --> 01:22:03.080
contributed to the being of the auspicious Devi.

01:22:04.999 --> 01:22:08.160
Then looking at Her, who had come into being

01:22:08.360 --> 01:22:11.040
from the assembled lights of all the devas,

01:22:11.240 --> 01:22:16.440
the immortals who were oppressed by Mahisasura experienced joy.

01:22:18.999 --> 01:22:21.999
The bearer of Pinaka

01:22:22.200 --> 01:22:27.440
drawing forth a trident from his own trident presented it to Her;

01:22:28.080 --> 01:22:33.999
and Vishnu bringing forth a discus out of his own discus gave Her.

01:22:35.280 --> 01:22:39.480
Varuna gave Her a conch, Agni a spear;

01:22:39.999 --> 01:22:45.920
and Maruta gave a bow as well as two quivers full of arrows.

01:22:47.999 --> 01:22:51.999
Indra, lord of devas, bringing forth a thunderbolt

01:22:52.160 --> 01:22:54.840
out of his own thunderbolt

01:22:54.999 --> 01:22:58.999
and a bell from that of His elephant Airavata, gave Her.

01:23:00.400 --> 01:23:04.360
Yama gave a staff from his own staff of Death

01:23:04.999 --> 01:23:08.999
and Varuna, the lord of waters, a noose;

01:23:09.999 --> 01:23:12.360
and Brahma, the lord of beings,

01:23:12.999 --> 01:23:17.999
gave a string of beads and a water-pot.

01:23:20.440 --> 01:23:25.200
Surya bestowed His own rays on all the pores of Her skin

01:23:25.920 --> 01:23:31.240
and Kala gave a spotless sword and a shield.

01:23:33.360 --> 01:23:37.999
The milk-ocean gave a pure necklace,

01:23:39.240 --> 01:23:45.200
a pair of garments, a divine crest-jewel, a pair of ear-rings,

01:23:45.440 --> 01:23:49.120
bracelets, a brilliant half-moon

01:23:49.320 --> 01:23:53.840
armlets on all arms, a pair of shining anklets,

01:23:53.999 --> 01:23:58.880
a unique necklace and excellent rings on all the fingers.

01:24:00.240 --> 01:24:03.840
Visvakarman gave her a very brilliant axe,

01:24:03.999 --> 01:24:09.280
weapons of various forms and also an impenetrable armour.

01:24:09.999 --> 01:24:15.040
The ocean gave her a garland of unfading lotuses for Her head,

01:24:15.240 --> 01:24:17.360
and another for her breast,

01:24:17.960 --> 01:24:22.240
besides a very beautiful lotus in her hand.

01:24:22.999 --> 01:24:30.320
The mountain Himavat gave her a lion to ride on a various jewels.

01:24:31.999 --> 01:24:34.160
The lord of wealth Kubera

01:24:34.360 --> 01:24:38.360
gave Her a drinking cup ever full of wine.

01:24:39.240 --> 01:24:42.840
Sesha, the lord of all serpents,

01:24:42.999 --> 01:24:47.440
who supports this earth, gave Her a serpent-necklace

01:24:47.999 --> 01:24:51.120
bedecked with best jewels.

01:24:51.960 --> 01:24:58.080
Rustom has given Me something, bracelet but I haven't brought it.

01:25:01.480 --> 01:25:06.480
Brought it from, he's brought it from Riad.

01:25:08.880 --> 01:25:11.960
From the Arab countries.

01:25:12.920 --> 01:25:14.400
All right.

01:25:15.480 --> 01:25:21.000
Honored likewise by other devas also with ornaments and weapons,

01:25:21.999 --> 01:25:28.000
the Devi gave out a loud roar with a defying laugh again and again.

01:25:30.200 --> 01:25:31.999
What's that?

01:25:32.999 --> 01:25:34.999
[Weakening].

01:25:37.880 --> 01:25:40.280
Honored likewise by other devas

01:25:40.480 --> 01:25:43.480
also with ornaments and weapons,

01:25:43.999 --> 01:25:46.999
the Devi gave out a loud roar

01:25:47.440 --> 01:25:50.999
with a defying laugh again and again.

01:25:53.999 --> 01:25:58.400
By her unending, exceedingly great, terrible roar

01:25:58.999 --> 01:26:01.840
the entire sky was filled,

01:26:01.999 --> 01:26:03.000
What are you saying?

01:26:03.200 --> 01:26:08.120
The entire sky was filled by Her roar.

01:26:08.999 --> 01:26:12.200
and there was great reverberation.

01:26:12.960 --> 01:26:16.999
All worlds shook, the seas trembled.

01:26:18.240 --> 01:26:22.360
The earth quaked and all the mountains rocked.

01:26:22.999 --> 01:26:29.999
"Victory to you", exclaimed the devas in joy to Her, the lion-rider.

01:26:30.999 --> 01:26:35.999
The sages, who bowed their bodies in devotion, extolled her.

01:26:36.999 --> 01:26:41.840
Seeing the three worlds agitated, the foes of devas,

01:26:41.999 --> 01:26:45.840
mobilized all their armies and rose up together

01:26:45.999 --> 01:26:49.400
with uplifted weapons.

01:26:50.999 --> 01:26:55.160
Mahishasura, exclaiming in wrath, 'Ha! What is this?'

01:26:55.999 --> 01:27:01.160
rushed towards that roar, surrounded by the innumerable asuras.

01:27:02.080 --> 01:27:06.240
Then he saw the Devi pervading the three worlds with her lustre.

01:27:06.999 --> 01:27:09.040
Lustre? I don't know.

01:27:14.280 --> 01:27:18.880
Making the earth bend with Her footstep,

01:27:20.880 --> 01:27:23.999
scraping the sky with Her diadem,

01:27:24.999 --> 01:27:29.480
shaking the nether worlds with the twang of Her bowstring,

01:27:29.999 --> 01:27:32.960
and standing there pervading all the quarters around

01:27:33.120 --> 01:27:35.240
with her thousand arms.

01:27:36.360 --> 01:27:41.840
Then began a battle between that Devi and the enemies of the devas,

01:27:41.999 --> 01:27:45.360
in which the quarters of the sky were illumined

01:27:45.920 --> 01:27:49.960
by the weapons and arms hurled diversely.

01:27:51.999 --> 01:27:57.840
Mahisasura's general, a great asura named Chiksura and Chamara,

01:27:57.999 --> 01:28:03.240
attended by forces comprising four parts, and other asuras fought.

01:28:05.200 --> 01:28:09.200
A great asura named Udagraha with sixty thousand chariots,

01:28:09.400 --> 01:28:11.999
and Mahahanu with ten millions

01:28:12.160 --> 01:28:14.999
Must be the one with so many Rolls Royces.

01:28:19.999 --> 01:28:22.160
Can be.

01:28:29.999 --> 01:28:35.400
and Mahahanu with ten millions of chariots gave battle.

01:28:36.999 --> 01:28:41.840
Asiloman, another great asura, with fifteen millions of chariots,

01:28:41.999 --> 01:28:47.160
and Bashkala with six millions fought in that battle.

01:28:48.999 --> 01:28:53.000
Privarita with many thousands of elephants and horses,

01:28:53.360 --> 01:28:56.920
and surrounded by ten millions of chariots, fought in that battle.

01:28:57.080 --> 01:29:01.280
Just imagine. So you can understand these rakshasas

01:29:01.960 --> 01:29:05.000
in modern times also are having so many Rolls Royces,

01:29:05.200 --> 01:29:06.840
so many people following them,

01:29:06.999 --> 01:29:08.800
thousands and thousands, look at that.

01:29:08.999 --> 01:29:10.960
And only one Goddess to fight.

01:29:19.999 --> 01:29:22.920
An asura named Bidala

01:29:23.080 --> 01:29:29.200
fought in that battle surrounded by five crores of chariots.

01:29:29.999 --> 01:29:32.920
Crores.

01:29:34.400 --> 01:29:40.960
I mean a chariot I think is equal to the price of a one hundred

01:29:41.120 --> 01:29:46.880
or maybe one thousand of Rolls Royces. So it's all right.

01:29:47.160 --> 01:29:50.480
They have completed their amount.

01:29:54.160 --> 01:29:57.920
And other great asuras, thousands in number,

01:29:58.080 --> 01:30:01.280
surrounded with chariots, elephants and horses

01:30:01.880 --> 01:30:03.400
fought with the Devi in that battle.

01:30:03.960 --> 01:30:08.840
Now you should understand how the asuras had such a powerful army,

01:30:08.999 --> 01:30:10.440
had so many people to fight,

01:30:10.999 --> 01:30:14.840
had such big elephants and all those things

01:30:14.999 --> 01:30:18.040
showing how much money they must be having.

01:30:18.999 --> 01:30:22.320
And that's what you see today also, same thing.

01:30:22.880 --> 01:30:25.840
They have all the money, they have all the chariots,

01:30:25.999 --> 01:30:29.400
they have everything, elephants and everything to fight,

01:30:30.200 --> 01:30:32.840
but they are not successful.

01:30:45.440 --> 01:30:48.840
Mahishasura was surrounded in the battle

01:30:48.999 --> 01:30:53.960
with thousands or crores of hordes, horses, elephants and chariots.

01:30:55.320 --> 01:30:59.480
Other asuras fought in the battle against the Devi

01:30:59.999 --> 01:31:04.240
with iron maces and javelins, with spears and clubs,

01:31:04.440 --> 01:31:08.999
with swords, axes and halberds.

01:31:09.840 --> 01:31:13.999
Some hurled spears and others nooses.

01:31:14.960 --> 01:31:19.999
They began to strike Her with swords in order to kill Her.

01:31:20.999 --> 01:31:25.160
Showering Her own weapons and arms, that Devi Chandika

01:31:25.880 --> 01:31:30.440
very easily cut into pieces all those weapons and arms.

01:31:33.999 --> 01:31:36.880
Without any strain on Her face

01:31:37.040 --> 01:31:40.280
and with gods and sages extolling her,

01:31:40.480 --> 01:31:45.999
the Ishvari threw Her weapons and arms at the bodies of the asuras.

01:31:46.960 --> 01:31:50.920
And the lion also which carried the Devi

01:31:51.080 --> 01:31:53.920
shaking its mane in rage,

01:31:54.080 --> 01:31:56.920
stalked among the hordes of the asuras

01:31:57.080 --> 01:32:00.480
like a conflagration amidst the forest.

01:32:01.999 --> 01:32:05.960
The side which Ambika, engaged in the battle,

01:32:06.120 --> 01:32:10.999
heaved became at once her battalions by hundreds and thousands.

01:32:12.080 --> 01:32:15.160
Energized by the power of the Devi,

01:32:15.400 --> 01:32:19.240
these battalions fought with battle-axes, javelins, swords

01:32:19.999 --> 01:32:22.920
and destroyed the asuras.

01:32:23.880 --> 01:32:27.840
All these battalions, some beat drums,

01:32:27.999 --> 01:32:31.920
some blew conches and others played on tabors

01:32:32.080 --> 01:32:35.400
in that great martial festival.

01:32:36.080 --> 01:32:41.160
Then the Devi killed hundreds of asuras with Her trident, club,

01:32:41.840 --> 01:32:45.840
showers of spears, swords and the like,

01:32:46.160 --> 01:32:51.400
and threw down others who were stupefied by the noise of Her bell;

01:32:52.280 --> 01:32:58.080
and binding others with Her noose, She dragged them on the ground.

01:32:58.960 --> 01:33:04.240
Some were split into two by the sharp slashes of Her sword,

01:33:04.800 --> 01:33:07.840
and others, smashed by the blows of Her mace,

01:33:07.999 --> 01:33:09.960
lay down on the ground;

01:33:10.120 --> 01:33:15.920
and some severely hammered by Her club vomited forth blood.

01:33:19.080 --> 01:33:24.880
Pierced in the breast by her trident, some fell on the ground.

01:33:25.040 --> 01:33:29.840
Pierced all over by Her arrows and resembling porcupines,

01:33:29.999 --> 01:33:33.160
some of the enemies of devas gave up their lives

01:33:33.400 --> 01:33:35.960
on that field of battle.

01:33:36.120 --> 01:33:41.320
Some had their arms cut off, some, their necks broken

01:33:41.480 --> 01:33:44.920
the heads of others rolled down;

01:33:45.080 --> 01:33:50.880
some others were torn asunder in the middle of their trunks,

01:33:51.040 --> 01:33:57.280
and some great asuras fell on the ground with their legs severed.

01:33:59.999 --> 01:34:03.320
Some rendered one-armed, one-eyed,

01:34:03.999 --> 01:34:07.999
and one-legged were again clove in twain by the Devi.

01:34:08.440 --> 01:34:14.920
And others, though rendered headless, fell and rose again.

01:34:15.999 --> 01:34:18.320
Headless trunks fought with the Devi

01:34:18.800 --> 01:34:21.400
with best weapons in their hands.

01:34:21.999 --> 01:34:26.000
Some of these headless trunks danced there in the battle

01:34:26.240 --> 01:34:29.120
to the rhythm of the musical instruments.

01:34:30.000 --> 01:34:34.840
The trunks of some other great asuras, with their swords,

01:34:34.999 --> 01:34:37.840
spears and lances still in their hands,

01:34:37.999 --> 01:34:43.840
shouted at the Devi with their just severed heads, 'Stop, stop'.

01:34:43.999 --> 01:34:46.920
That part of earth where the battle was fought

01:34:47.080 --> 01:34:48.999
became impassable with the asuras,

01:34:49.160 --> 01:34:53.120
elephants and horses and chariots that had been felled.

01:34:55.999 --> 01:35:00.400
The profuse blood from the asuras, elephants and horses

01:35:00.840 --> 01:35:05.999
flowed immediately like large rivers amidst that army of the asuras.

01:35:07.280 --> 01:35:12.280
As fire consumes a huge heap of straw and wood,

01:35:12.800 --> 01:35:18.920
so did Ambika destroy that vast army of asuras in no time.

01:35:21.280 --> 01:35:28.080
And her carrier-lion, thundering aloud with quivering mane,

01:35:28.999 --> 01:35:32.840
prowled about in the battlefield,

01:35:32.999 --> 01:35:35.200
appearing to search out the vital breaths

01:35:35.400 --> 01:35:38.480
from the bodies of the enemies of devas.

01:35:39.040 --> 01:35:42.240
In that battlefield the battalions of the Devi

01:35:42.440 --> 01:35:44.880
fought in such a manner with the asuras

01:35:45.040 --> 01:35:50.999
that the devas in heaven, showering flowers, extolled them.

